---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="min-[1100px]:hidden">
    <main class="flex min-h-screen items-center justify-center px-5 py-10">
      <section class="glass-panel w-full max-w-md rounded-[30px] p-7 text-center">
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" class="mx-auto h-16 w-16 rounded-2xl" />
        <p class="eyebrow mt-6">Desktop only</p>
        <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">This landing page is tuned for desktop.</h1>
        <p class="mt-5 leading-7 text-rough-muted">The hero composition and review-surface visual are intentionally desktop-first. Open it on a larger screen to see the intended layout.</p>
        <div class="mt-7 flex justify-center">
          <a class="button-base button-primary" href="/../README.md">Open the Project</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto hidden w-[min(1240px,calc(100vw-32px))] pb-24 pt-6 min-[1100px]:block">
    <header class="glass-panel sticky top-4 z-20 mb-9 flex flex-col gap-5 rounded-full px-5 py-4 md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between">
      <a class="flex w-fit items-center gap-3.5" href="#top" aria-label="Roughcut Stdio home">
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" class="h-10 w-10 rounded-xl" />
        <span class="text-base font-bold tracking-[0.02em] text-rough-text">Roughcut Stdio</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 text-sm text-rough-muted" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="transition hover:text-rough-text focus-visible:text-rough-text" href="#features">Features</a>
        <a class="transition hover:text-rough-text focus-visible:text-rough-text" href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a class="transition hover:text-rough-text focus-visible:text-rough-text" href="#proof">Proof</a>
        <a class="transition hover:text-rough-text focus-visible:text-rough-text" href="#cta">Get Started</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="top" class="space-y-9">
      <section class="grid gap-11 py-8 min-[1100px]:grid-cols-[0.94fr_minmax(0,1.06fr)] min-[1100px]:items-center">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Local-first footage screening for editors</p>
          <h1 class="max-w-[11ch] text-[clamp(3rem,7vw,6.2rem)] font-extrabold leading-[0.93] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">Skip the scrub. Start from a rough cut.</h1>
          <p class="mt-5 max-w-[60ch] text-[1.08rem] leading-7 text-rough-muted">Roughcut Stdio scans raw footage, surfaces the strongest candidate moments, grades them, and assembles a first-pass timeline so you can move from ingest to editorial review faster.</p>
          <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3.5">
            <a class="button-base button-primary" href="#cta">Launch the Workflow</a>
            <a class="button-base button-secondary" href="/../docs/desktop-distribution.md">Read Desktop Docs</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-2.5" aria-label="Product signals">
            <li class="chip">Offline-capable packaged runtime</li>
            <li class="chip">Deterministic fallback paths</li>
            <li class="chip">DaVinci Resolve export</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal relative min-h-[640px]">
          <div class="halo halo--mint"></div>
          <div class="halo halo--gold"></div>

          <div class="absolute right-0 top-8 w-[min(680px,calc(100vw-500px))] min-w-[560px] max-w-[680px]">
            <div class="relative" data-tilt-card>
              <div class="visual-card glass-panel overflow-hidden rounded-[30px]">
                <div class="flex gap-2 px-4 py-3">
                  <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
                  <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
                  <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-white/20"></span>
                </div>
                <img src="/app.png" alt="Roughcut Stdio desktop review interface" class="w-full rounded-b-[30px]" />
              </div>

              <div class="floating-note absolute -right-3 top-[84px] z-10 w-[232px]">
                <strong>Review-first</strong>
                <span>Best takes, grades, provenance, export.</span>
              </div>

              <div class="floating-note absolute -left-5 bottom-[78px] z-10 w-[220px]">
                <strong>4-phase pipeline</strong>
                <span>Discover, analyze, select, assemble.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Runtime</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Packaged</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Bundled Python, analyzer environment, media tools, and export helpers.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Storage</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">App-managed</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Generated state, logs, caches, and model assets live outside the repo.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
          <span class="detail-kicker">Fallback</span>
          <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Graceful</strong>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Optional runtimes can degrade without dead-ending the workflow.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="features" class="pt-3">
        <div class="reveal mb-6 max-w-3xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
          <h2 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.4rem)] font-extrabold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">Built for editors who need selects, not another dashboard.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">01</span>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Screen footage locally</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Scan a large media set on-device, without pushing footage into a cloud review service.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">02</span>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Refine into usable segments</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Turn seed regions into more complete candidate moments, with transcript and semantic support when available.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">03</span>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Score and compare quickly</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Surface technical, semantic, and story signals in one review surface instead of scrubbing every clip manually.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.18em] text-rough-warn">04</span>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Assemble the first pass</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Review the generated timeline, promote the best take, and export straight into DaVinci Resolve.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="workflow" class="pt-3">
        <div class="reveal mb-6 max-w-3xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">How it flows</p>
          <h2 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.4rem)] font-extrabold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">One clear path from media folder to editorial handoff.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">1</div>
            <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Choose the footage</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Select a media folder and configure the runtime once. Packaged mode owns storage and setup.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">2</div>
            <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Process with the right stack</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Run deterministic, transcript-backed, or local-AI analysis depending on what assets are available.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">3</div>
            <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Review what matters</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Inspect graded sections, provenance, and timeline choices through a dark, editorial review surface.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="workflow-step reveal glass-panel relative min-h-[220px] overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <div class="mb-[18px] inline-flex h-[42px] w-[42px] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rough-accent/15 font-extrabold text-rough-accent">4</div>
            <h3 class="text-[1.32rem] font-bold text-rough-text">Export the cut</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-7 text-rough-muted">Push the current review state to FCPXML for DaVinci Resolve and keep working in your existing pipeline.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="proof" class="grid gap-4 pt-3 xl:grid-cols-[0.94fr_minmax(0,1.06fr)] xl:items-start">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Why it feels different</p>
          <h2 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.4rem)] font-extrabold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">More like a post workflow. Less like AI theater.</h2>
          <p class="mt-5 leading-7 text-rough-muted">The visual system is intentionally restrained: dark panels, clear status states, and signal-forward summaries. The product focuses on runtime readiness, editorial confidence, and exportable output rather than novelty UI.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-4">
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Ready state</span>
            <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Bundled runtime vs model assets</strong>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">The app separates core runtime health from optional model bootstrap so users can recover cleanly.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Artifact continuity</span>
            <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Generated outputs stay inspectable</strong>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Project JSON, diagnostics, benchmark history, logs, and export state remain part of the review flow.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="reveal glass-panel rounded-[22px] p-6">
            <span class="detail-kicker">Modern fallback</span>
            <strong class="block text-base text-rough-text">Reduced capability still ships work</strong>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-rough-muted">Transcript, CLIP, and provider-specific AI can degrade cleanly instead of blocking progress.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="cta" class="reveal pt-3">
        <div class="glass-panel relative overflow-hidden rounded-[30px] px-7 py-10 md:px-10">
          <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,rgba(95,209,166,0.2),transparent_32%),radial-gradient(circle_at_bottom_left,rgba(255,202,107,0.14),transparent_24%)]"></div>
          <div class="relative">
            <p class="eyebrow">Ready to package the workflow</p>
            <h2 class="max-w-4xl text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.4rem)] font-extrabold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.04em] text-rough-text">Move from raw footage to usable shot selection faster.</h2>
            <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl leading-7 text-rough-muted">Roughcut Stdio keeps the product local-first, dark-mode native, and editor-facing from the first launch through export.</p>
            <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3.5">
              <a class="button-base button-primary" href="/../README.md">Open the Project</a>
              <a class="button-base button-secondary" href="/../docs/setup.md">Setup Guide</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
